abstract_ssm: This collection consists of attorney George Nicolau's arbitration decisions and awards. George Nicolau has worked as a labor arbitrator since the 1970s, most notably serving as the chief arbitrator for Major League Baseball from 1986 to 1995. Nicolau's arbitration decisisons are mostly dated between 1970 and 2010, and cover a variety of trades including the airline, entertainment, communications, health, and sports industries.
